I might've expected this of Phoebe. But,Ryan,you're a military man.
我相信你会这样，菲比 但是莱恩，你是个军人呀

169
00:11:10,67 --> 00:11:14,36
You and Milton have to join us on the boat. Bring the kids.
你跟米顿得来坐我们的船 带孩子们来

170
00:11:14,64 --> 00:11:16,07
We'll make a day of it.
咱们好好玩一天

171
00:11:16,30 --> 00:11:19,00
That sounds lovely. We'll have to set it up.
听起来好棒 我们得好好安排一下

172
00:11:19,21 --> 00:11:21,90
I better get back. Hope the baby feels better.
我最好回去了 希望宝宝好点了

173
00:11:22,14 --> 00:11:23,80
Thanks.
谢谢

174
00:11:24,05 --> 00:11:26,17
-Bye-bye,Jeannie. -Bye-bye,Joseph.
谢了，拜拜，金妮 拜拜，乔瑟

175
00:11:26,81 --> 00:11:28,37
What a phony.
好虚伪

176
00:11:31,35 --> 00:11:34,84
You'll teach her a lesson when she steps off the dock onto nothing.
我相信她在码头一脚 踩了个空的时候她就会学乖了

177
00:11:36,49 --> 00:11:38,22
-Hey,Mr. Douglas. -Sir.
岛先生 日安

178
00:11:38,43 --> 00:11:42,83
Bing,I got your memo. We're not gonna see the report until next Friday?
听着，备忘录我收到了 系统报告下周五才会出来？

179
00:11:43,03 --> 00:11:45,66
My group wants to spend the holiday with family.
我组里的人希望这个周末 能够跟家人一起共度

180
00:11:45,90 --> 00:11:48,70
I have a family. I'm gonna be here.
我也有家庭 但我还是会来这儿

181
00:11:48,90 --> 00:11:51,06
Yeah,Bing. What's that about?
是啊，老宾，你干嘛呢？

182
00:11:56,04 --> 00:11:59,07
It's about cutting them a little slack for morale.
我要让我的人稍微喘一口气 以提高士气

183
00:11:59,38 --> 00:12:02,18
Look,I can get some rough numbers by Wednesday.
如果你想看大概数字 我可以在星期三以前给你

184
00:12:02,42 --> 00:12:04,44
Rough numbers?
大概数字？

185
00:12:05,55 --> 00:12:09,61
This company wasn't built on rough numbers. Right,Mr. Douglas?
公司不是建在大概数字上 我说得对吗，岛先生？

186
00:12:10,19 --> 00:12:13,02
Have the final numbers on my desk by Tuesday.
星期二以前 把正确数字放在我桌上

187
00:12:13,23 --> 00:12:14,92
If you say so,sir.
照你的意思做吧

188
00:12:16,13 --> 00:12:18,22
Joseph's good,isn't he?
乔瑟很行，是不是？

189
00:12:20,30 --> 00:12:21,96
I'm going to kill you.
乔伊，我要杀了你

190
00:12:23,07 --> 00:12:27,47
Hey,I just figured Joseph's the kind of guy who likes to mix it up.
乔瑟是那种喜欢争的人

191
00:12:27,71 --> 00:12:30,94
You know,get in there, ruffle some feathers.
你知道，一头钻入，兴风作浪

192
00:12:32,15 --> 00:12:33,37
Why?
为什么？

193
00:12:35,32 --> 00:12:38,48
Look,I'm sorry, but that's what Joseph does.
听着，抱歉，但乔瑟就是那样

194
00:12:39,09 --> 00:12:41,11
Okay? If you try to pull something...
你想耍花招的话…

195
00:12:41,56 --> 00:12:43,22
... he'll call you on it.
…他会揭发你

196
00:12:43,72 --> 00:12:46,22
"What are you trying to pull?" he'll say.
他会说“你耍什么花招？”

197
00:12:51,63 --> 00:12:52,46
Duct tape.
电线胶带

198
00:12:53,00 --> 00:12:54,93
Was I supposed to bring something too?
我是不是也该带点什么来？

199
00:12:56,44 --> 00:13:00,27
This is for the scratchy twins. I taped oven mitts to their hands.
这是给那对痒鸳鸯的 我把手套帖在他们手上

200
00:13:01,48 --> 00:13:02,94
You're strict.
你真严

201
00:13:03,14 --> 00:13:05,01
Well,it's for their own good.
这是为他们好啊

202
00:13:05,25 --> 00:13:09,77
You know,I like the way you have efficiently folded this tab under.
摩妮卡，我很欣赏你有效率的 把胶带的一端折起来

203
00:13:10,08 --> 00:13:14,35
See,in a tape emergency you could shave valuable seconds off your time.
你看，急需用胶带的时候 可省下好几秒宝贵的时间

204
00:13:15,82 --> 00:13:17,59
Exactly!
正是

205
00:13:18,13 --> 00:13:22,03
God,I love that I can be totally neurotic around you now.
真高兴在你面前 可以完全的神经过敏

206
00:13:22,86 --> 00:13:23,85
Tell me the truth.
告诉我实话

207
00:13:24,13 --> 00:13:27,33
Don't you like having everything on your desk perpendicular?
现在你桌上的一切都是直角的 不是好多了吗？

208
00:13:27,54 --> 00:13:30,70
If it's not a right angle, it is a wrong angle.
如果它们不是直角 那就是错角

209
00:13:31,64 --> 00:13:32,70
-Very good. -Thank you.
很好 谢谢

210
00:13:32,97 --> 00:13:35,64
Tomorrow,I'm gonna do your clocks.
你知道吗？ 明天我要改你的时钟

211
00:13:36,61 --> 00:13:38,48
You're gonna do what to my clocks?
你要怎样改我的时钟？

212
00:13:38,78 --> 00:13:40,14
Set them to my time.
我要把它调成我的时间

213
00:13:42,72 --> 00:13:43,77
I'm confused.
这我搞糊涂了

214
00:13:44,02 --> 00:13:46,28
I thought we shared time.
时间不是都一样的吗？

215
00:13:47,15 --> 00:13:51,49
No. See,in my bedroom I set my clock six minutes fast.
不…瞧 我把房间的时钟调快了六分钟

216
00:13:51,73 --> 00:13:52,62
Wanna know why?
想不想知道原因？

217
00:13:52,86 --> 00:13:57,30
Because it's in a slightly different time zone than the kitchen?
因为跟厨房在不同的时区里

218
00:13:57,57 --> 00:13:58,53
Forget it.
算了，我不想要说了

219
00:13:58,80 --> 00:14:00,06
No,come on,tell me.
来嘛，告诉我嘛

220
00:14:00,33 --> 00:14:02,13
-You don't understand. -Come on.
不，因为你不会明白 来嘛

221
00:14:02,34 --> 00:14:04,36
You don't have any obsessive things.
不，你根本没有 任何可爱的小怪癖

222
00:14:04,57 --> 00:14:06,40
No,that's not true.
那不对…

223
00:14:06,64 --> 00:14:08,73
Oh,yeah? Tell me one of yours.
是吗？ 好吧，说一个来听听

224
00:14:15,72 --> 00:14:20,24
One of my things is I always separate my sweat socks...
譬如说吧，我总是 把我的运动袜…

225
00:14:20,52 --> 00:14:22,92
...from my dress socks.
…跟西装袜分开来摆

226
00:14:25,86 --> 00:14:27,38
What if they get mixed up?
如果搞混了会怎样？

227
00:14:27,60 --> 00:14:29,53
Boy,I would just....
天啊，那我会…

228
00:14:30,60 --> 00:14:31,90
I would freak out.
我会发狂

229
00:14:34,07 --> 00:14:35,54
You would not.
你才不会

230
00:14:35,77 --> 00:14:39,36
I can't believe this. I hate this. You're too normal.
我真不敢相信 真讨厌你那么正常

231
00:14:39,57 --> 00:14:41,67
I can't believe you don't have a "thing."
真不敢相信我的男友没怪癖

232
00:14:41,88 --> 00:14:44,44
My boyfriend doesn't have a "thing."
我的男友没有怪癖

233
00:14:44,68 --> 00:14:47,88
See,if anyone overheard that, I didn't come off well.
如果有人听到你这句话 别人会怀疑我无能

234
00:14:57,12 --> 00:15:01,93
-Mr. Douglas is looking for you. -Why is Mr. Douglas looking for me?
岛先生正在找你 为什么要找我？

235
00:15:02,63 --> 00:15:06,19
He suspects you dropped the ball on the Lender project.
因为他怀疑 你搞砸那个连纳方案

236
00:15:07,07 --> 00:15:09,63
